raud if the public statements=C2=A0are false. But suing for a=C2=A0breach o=
f fiduciary duties=C2=A0seems odder: The essential claim here is that the d=
irectors prioritized the business interests of the company over truth, ethi=
cs, US democracy, etc. Which is=C2=A0bad, but not necessarily bad=C2=A0for =
shareholders.

