 #ccc;">  theory</a> is that if a company says publicly that it has good et=
hics, and then it turns out that in fact it did unethical things, and the s=
tock drops, then shareholders will sue for fraud; fine. (Fox=E2=80=99s stoc=
k is <em>up</em> since the 2020 election but never mind.)=C2=A0You can sue =
for=C2=A0<em>securities fraud </em>if the public statements=C2=A0are false.=
